               </messagepanel>
            </hazardstatement>
            <p class="- topic/p ">Make the following checks
annually:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Perform both the <xref href="Monthly_Check_CPT_0000327541.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/> and <xref href="Semi-Annual_Check_CPT_0000327540.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Isolate <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">the system/unit with the manual
bypass switch or turn it off</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">and turn off the
system/unit</ph>, see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Operating Manual</i> for more information.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the system is dusty, clean the system from dust with a vacuum
cleaner.<note class="- topic/note "> Do not use any liquid to clean!</note>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Perform the recommended maintenance for
batteries supplied from Reality, see chapter <xref href="Annual_Battery_Check_CPT_0000415775.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>. For batteries not supplied by Reality follow
the maintenance recommendations by the original equipment manufacturer
(OEM).</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for systems with bypass mains voltage
stabilizer T090:</b> Check if the bypass stabilizer needs to be cleaned,
lubricated or if any parts are worn. For more information see the
section <xref href="Check_the_bypass_stabilizer_T090_CPT_0000413871.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref ">Check the bypass stabilizer T090</xref>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If applicable, check and follow any annual maintenance recommendations
by other original equipment manufacturer (OEM).</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Re-install any removed protection covers.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Turn on the system or unit, see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Operating Manual</i> for more information.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Perform a functional check of the system to verify that the
system switches correctly between operating modes (according to operation
mode priority). See chapter <xref href="Function_Check_of_the_System_CPT_0000413872.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for systems with an ISBS solution: </b>Perform a function check of the ISBS solution to check that the ISBS
takes over if the controller board is inoperable. See chapter <xref href="Function_Check_of_the_ISBS_Solution_CPT_0000387702.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
